Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.47,0:00:26.22,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Memories from ten years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.14,0:00:29.68,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The words of the man who was my dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.60,0:00:36.23,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even if I was a mistake from the beginning, \Nthe path I've chosen isn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.61,0:00:41.61,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To ensure that event wouldn't \Nbe just some tragic past,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.61,0:00:44.53,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to become a hero of justice.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.74,0:00:48.03,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,For ten years, I've embraced the ideal
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.20,0:00:52.87,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,of a time when everyone would be \Nhappy and no one would cry.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.63,0:01:01.59,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So it was clear from the beginning \Nwhat I needed to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.05,0:01:05.76,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't fight because I became a Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.64,0:01:11.89,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I decided to fight because it was \Nsomething that I could do.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.89,0:01:14.48,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Something I believed I ought to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.86,0:01:26.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Tohsaka...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.21,0:03:04.55,Title,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(232,513)}#13   Time of Departure
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.28,0:03:27.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How brave you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.53,0:03:30.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You can continue to defy me all you like,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.32,0:03:34.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,but your Servant body cannot resist me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.16,0:03:38.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Surely you can sense my Command Seals \Neating away at you, little by little.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.62,0:03:44.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Would it not be easier if you simply \Ngave in and submitted to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.34,0:03:48.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, my stubborn Saber...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.55,0:03:50.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing, Caster?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.18,0:03:53.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Souichirou-sama...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.18,0:03:55.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you here?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.64,0:04:00.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I requested for you to \Nremain at Ryuudou Temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.14,0:04:03.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Answer my question first, Caster.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.02,0:04:06.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Answer me. What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.57,0:04:12.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yesterday, I seized the Servant of Emiya Shirou,\None of the other Masters.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.53,0:04:17.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He escaped just before I could finish him, \Nbut he is no longer a Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.66,0:04:18.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.83,0:04:22.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But I do not remember instructing you to do so.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.04,0:04:24.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I acted on my own authority, Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.88,0:04:29.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I attacked this church in order to \Nobtain the Holy Grail's vessel.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.05,0:04:31.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I slew the priest who was the overseer,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.09,0:04:35.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,but the Grail's whereabouts remain unknown.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.01,0:04:39.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You failed to return because you \Ncouldn't locate the Grail?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.27,0:04:42.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I get the gist of the situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.39,0:04:45.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Now, can you explain why \Nyou acted on your own?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.11,0:04:47.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I apologize.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.61,0:04:50.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,However, my actions were all for you, Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.44,0:04:55.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My only goal is to help you achieve victory.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.32,0:04:58.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There is no other reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.79,0:05:00.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.66,0:05:04.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, you cannot leave this place.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.12,0:05:07.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Search it until you are satisfied.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.04,0:05:10.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Until then, I will also remain here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.26,0:05:13.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, that will not be necessary, Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.47,0:05:17.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Locating the Holy Grail will take some time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.47,0:05:21.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It would be safer for you to \Nreturn to Ryuudou Temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.98,0:05:23.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A fair point.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.73,0:05:27.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But if I did so, I would be unable \Nto achieve my own objective.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.65,0:05:29.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Souichirou-sama, what is...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.11,0:05:33.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Be quick about it. If it isn't here, so be it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.20,0:05:38.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't care how you accomplish it. \NAll I need is the result.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.09,0:05:53.55,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When was it that I finally figured \Nout what that dream really was?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.97,0:05:58.18,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That it was a certain Heroic \NSpirit's mental landscape.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.89,0:06:02.14,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Among many Heroic Spirits, the Servants,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.39,0:06:07.52,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,there are special Servants that are \Nsafeguards, called "Protectors."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.52,0:06:10.27,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They are summoned into the various ages,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.27,0:06:12.94,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and prevent the human world's destruction.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.65,0:06:15.78,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, more accurately,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.78,0:06:19.53,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,they prevent the human race from destroying itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.53,0:06:22.58,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even though he was summoned to save humanity,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.58,0:06:24.62,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,before he could save them,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.62,0:06:28.50,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,he was first forced to clean up the \Nmesses that humans had made.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.17,0:06:34.17,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It didn't take many summonings \Nfor him to determine that it was futile
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.17,0:06:36.59,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and start despising the human world.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.59,0:06:43.31,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In the end, he continued to be betrayed \Nby his ideal, even after death.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.78,0:06:59.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you aren't feeling well, we can put this off.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.49,0:07:04.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There's no pressing need to attack right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.20,0:07:09.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, if we know where Caster is, \Nwe should deal with her at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.25,0:07:13.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.97,0:07:21.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's creepy, watching me sleep \Ninstead of waking me up.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.26,0:07:22.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Relax.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.72,0:07:25.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I swear I wasn't doing anything so rude.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.64,0:07:27.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I did hear something, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.14,0:07:30.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You muttered some very harsh things,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.56,0:07:33.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,like "This is so irritating" and "I'm pissed."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.57,0:07:35.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's a relief.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.45,0:07:41.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Say, Archer...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.32,0:07:46.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Have you ever regretted the things you've done?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.25,0:07:50.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If I can help it, I want to avoid any regrets.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.00,0:07:54.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I bet that'll be hard, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.04,0:07:57.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even more than I imagine.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.71,0:08:00.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Some can do it, and some can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.59,0:08:04.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'd say that you are the former.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.10,0:08:07.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,People of that type don't make mistakes,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.97,0:08:11.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and they don't even think they'd make mistakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.81,0:08:12.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Rin...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.23,0:08:17.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Brilliant people shine more \Nbrightly than ordinary ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.69,0:08:22.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They never regret or agonize \Nover what they've done.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.91,0:08:26.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And you are most definitely that sort of person.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.83,0:08:32.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Tohsaka Rin can believe in her own path \Nto the very end without regret.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.92,0:08:37.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What about you, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.17,0:08:42.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Will you be able to believe that \Nyou're right to the very end?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.18,0:08:46.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, but that question is meaningless.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.89,0:08:48.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why is it meaningless?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.72,0:08:50.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Have you forgotten, Master?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.31,0:08:56.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My "end" came and went long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.74,0:09:08.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,She attacked the overseer? \NI'd say that's a bold move.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.20,0:09:11.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Kirei was probably prepared for it, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.41,0:09:14.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Rin, I must ask you again.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.25,0:09:17.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What, you're still worried?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.54,0:09:20.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll take on Caster.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.21,0:09:24.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you get too close, she might \Nuse Rule Breaker on you, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.63,0:09:28.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So, you see to her Master, Kuzuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.14,0:09:32.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm fine with taking on that man.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.56,0:09:37.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But do you understand that no \Nmage is a match for Caster?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.56,0:09:41.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Relax. If I didn't have a chance, \NI wouldn't have said it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.65,0:09:44.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You can leave her to me, Archer.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.28,0:09:48.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Very well. I'll trust in you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.99,0:09:51.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All right, let's do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.87,0:09:54.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll take out Caster here, no matter what.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.83,0:09:57.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And when I do, Saber will \Nprobably return to normal,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.83,0:10:01.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and be able to forge a new pact with Shirou, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.15,0:10:20.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So, did you make sure he was dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.52,0:10:22.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Saber...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.40,0:10:25.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And what is that supposed to mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.82,0:10:26.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.95,0:10:29.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you didn't see his corpse,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.07,0:10:32.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,he's still stubbornly clinging to \Nlife somewhere, that's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.12,0:10:35.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But enough about him. Let's get this over with.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.08,0:10:39.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This time, you don't have a human shield, \Nso I can go all out to beat you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.17,0:10:42.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think you can beat me in a magic battle?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.05,0:10:45.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It depends on how I go about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.09,0:10:48.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And thankfully, you don't seem to \Nhave full control of Saber yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.26,0:10:51.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Plus, I also know how strong Kuzuki-sensei is.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.47,0:10:53.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He's no match for my Archer.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.60,0:10:56.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you ready, Archer?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.60,0:10:57.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.48,0:11:00.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As planned, then, Rin?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.73,0:11:01.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.02,0:11:03.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don't hold back.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.69,0:11:06.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm using everything I have!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.41,0:11:13.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How adorable.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.16,0:11:16.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You think you have a chance \Nagainst me, one-on-one?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.67,0:11:22.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you forgetting my trump card?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.50,0:11:28.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,With my Command Seals, I can \Nmake her my puppet now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.05,0:11:33.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you use a Command Seal on her, \NSaber would be able to resist it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.26,0:11:35.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know if it would be for one minute or two,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.10,0:11:40.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,but that's more than enough time to take down
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.65,0:11:41.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,the likes of you!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.58,0:11:57.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A distraction?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.66,0:12:01.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll start by pulling you down from there!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.04,0:12:05.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Archer!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.18,0:12:20.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Archer?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.94,0:12:33.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think you're doing, Archer?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.70,0:12:40.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You see, defeating her here struck me as idealistic.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.58,0:12:44.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When it comes to escaping, she's the best there is.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.25,0:12:50.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,After all, she's a woman who would tear apart \Nher own younger brother to escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.17,0:12:53.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You talk as though you know all about me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.01,0:12:55.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know my true identity?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.30,0:12:58.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Familiars that use dragon teeth as vessels
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.97,0:13:01.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,are the hallmark of the King of Colchis's magecraft.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.77,0:13:07.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,His daughter, Princess Medea, \Nwas hailed as a witch without peer.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.32,0:13:10.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't believe it, he's...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.29,0:13:26.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If I may ask, Caster, do you \Nstill have reserves to spare?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.42,0:13:29.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Archer, are you...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.26,0:13:38.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.85,0:13:44.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I have sufficient mana to sustain not only \None more, but all the Servants!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.27,0:13:46.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then that simplifies things.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.60,0:13:51.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I will take you up on your earlier offer, Caster.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.40,0:13:55.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even though you turned me down before?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.91,0:13:57.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The situation has changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.66,0:13:59.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If Saber is under your control,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.83,0:14:03.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,isn't it only natural that I go \Nover to the winning side?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.67,0:14:08.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I distrust traitors.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.00,0:14:10.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As well you should.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.50,0:14:13.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm only yielding to you for my own benefit.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.88,0:14:16.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There is no trust or loyalty in that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.80,0:14:20.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But is that not how Servants are by nature?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.27,0:14:23.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.73,0:14:29.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If I could not control you myself, it would \Nspeak poorly of my abilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.31,0:14:33.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then I shall give you what you wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.08,0:14:45.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Tohsaka!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.43,0:15:00.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Trace... on!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.15,0:15:15.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Shirou, you idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.49,0:15:17.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think you're doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.57,0:15:20.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So that appears to be that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.66,0:15:25.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your rude interruption was a surprise, \Nbut the outcome remains unchanged.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.20,0:15:27.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I shall finish you here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.91,0:15:30.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No. Wait, Caster.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.04,0:15:36.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I want to attach one condition \Nto my joining your forces.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.51,0:15:38.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A condition?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.05,0:15:42.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I offered my freedom without resistance.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.05,0:15:46.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My price is that you let them leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.98,0:15:51.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,For all your words and actions, you're soft.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.77,0:15:55.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, I merely thought it would be \Nwrong for a Heroic Spirit
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.53,0:15:58.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,to cut down his heartbroken former Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.03,0:16:04.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hearing common decency from \Na traitor's mouth is odd.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.20,0:16:08.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Very well, I shall let them go.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.83,0:16:11.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But if they ever get in my way again...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.38,0:16:13.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.84,0:16:17.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If they are fools who would \Nembrace a hopeless fight,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.13,0:16:19.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,they will be cut down without mercy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.84,0:16:23.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go. For now, he's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.22,0:16:27.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you hate me, it is misplaced, Rin.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.06,0:16:31.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This woman is the superior Master, that's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.81,0:16:34.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I side with the most powerful.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.56,0:16:36.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.36,0:16:38.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But you'll regret it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.36,0:16:40.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll never quit.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.49,0:16:41.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You hear me?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.66,0:16:44.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll defeat Caster and take you back.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.41,0:16:46.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And when I do,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.79,0:16:51.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I won't forgive you, no matter \Nhow much you apologize.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.22,0:17:03.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's what you get for pulling a stunt like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.30,0:17:05.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Get some rest!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.72,0:17:09.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, let's get back to my place \Nas soon as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.39,0:17:11.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry, it doesn't hurt that much.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.56,0:17:12.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You can't be serious!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.85,0:17:17.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me it doesn't hurt, \Nnot with an injury like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.61,0:17:19.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, are you listening?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.28,0:17:21.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why is this even happening?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.99,0:17:24.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Couldn't you tell immediately \Nthat the church wasn't safe?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.74,0:17:27.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not that stupid. Of course I could tell!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.87,0:17:30.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then you should have turned right around, idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.20,0:17:32.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How could you try a projection with those injuries?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.66,0:17:35.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That'll only make things worse!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.42,0:17:38.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And you're telling me you aren't in pain?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.29,0:17:41.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I swear, you're so messed up!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.67,0:17:45.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, you're hurting worse than I am, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.05,0:17:47.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So let's go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.76,0:17:51.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You can gripe and moan once we get back.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.40,0:18:00.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.15,0:18:05.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe this. A guy made me cry.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.99,0:18:10.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,T-Tohsaka, my hand—
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.95,0:18:12.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.08,0:18:14.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're going to make this right, jerk.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.75,0:18:20.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Listen,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.75,0:18:23.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,don't you dare turn around.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.34,0:18:27.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you see my face, I'll get really mad.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.60,0:18:34.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Archer was right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.69,0:18:40.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I should have defeated Caster when I had \Nthe chance, no matter what it took.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.15,0:18:42.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not whining or anything,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.28,0:18:47.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,but I always mess up the most important thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.24,0:18:52.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I can handle the second or third \Nmost important thing easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.24,0:18:56.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But I always mess up the most important one.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.87,0:19:01.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I can't only blame him for going over to her side.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.96,0:19:03.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm beaten.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.59,0:19:06.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,After all I said,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.51,0:19:09.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I suddenly found myself cornered.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.47,0:19:15.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I think this is where you're \Nsupposed to say, "By what?"
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.56,0:19:19.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh. Then, cornered by what?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.90,0:19:25.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You said a thing like that, so I got \Neven more depressed that I failed.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.65,0:19:27.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's only temporary, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.95,0:19:31.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You haven't done anything \Nto beat yourself up over.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.70,0:19:33.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.41,0:19:38.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We're in this mess because \Nmy strategy was so wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.37,0:19:41.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That just means you failed at one thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.84,0:19:44.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But that doesn't mean you're wrong, Tohsaka.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.42,0:19:50.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To be honest, you look blindingly brilliant to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.51,0:19:52.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't regret things, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.85,0:19:57.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I believe what I've done was the right thing, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.73,0:20:00.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That belief is a mess of patches.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.81,0:20:03.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But once you get that regret out of your system,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.90,0:20:07.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I bet you'll pay them back twice over.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.61,0:20:15.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, why did you save me?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.25,0:20:22.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? How did you get that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.50,0:20:24.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, you can have it back.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.84,0:20:29.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I have another pendant just like it at my house.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.26,0:20:33.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,After Lancer nearly killed me at \Nschool, it was lying next to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.85,0:20:36.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I picked it up, and I've had it ever since.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.18,0:20:39.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You have one just like it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.89,0:20:44.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Did I say something strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.40,0:20:46.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, not really.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.48,0:20:51.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, why would this be a \Nreason for you to save me?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.78,0:20:53.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.79,0:21:02.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The truth is, that was an afterthought.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.58,0:21:04.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If I must confess,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.13,0:21:08.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I've always looked up to this \Ngirl named Tohsaka Rin.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.46,0:21:10.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then, inconvenient as it was...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.34,0:21:16.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When I finally got around to talking \Nto her, I fell for her even more.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.93,0:21:21.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So before I knew it, I had already jumped \Ndown there without thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.69,0:21:27.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hey, if you go around blurting out \Nthings like that without thinking,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.48,0:21:29.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,people will get the wrong idea!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.19,0:21:33.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I really do have feelings for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.45,0:21:37.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You jerk! You enormous jerk!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.08,0:21:47.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for coming to my rescue.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.46,0:21:51.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I was really happy that you saved me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.85,0:23:29.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I appreciate your thoughtfulness, \Nbut before that...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.15,0:23:32.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It works best when the raw materials are pure.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.02,0:23:34.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Could we work with other Masters?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.57,0:23:39.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You are about to die here, so is \Nthat any of your concern?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.36,0:23:40.01,Next,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(526,1)}Next Time \NThe Princess of Colchis
